{
  "text": "\u2022 Quantitative Estimation of Drug-likeness (QED): a 0 to 1 float value estimating how likely a molecule is a viable candidate for a drug. QED is meant to capture the abstract notion of aesthetics in medicinal chemistry [CITATION_1] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "205289650"
